If we have `p = q`, then by substituting `q` with `p` in the goal, we get `p.snd x x_1 = p.snd x x_1`, which is true by reflexivity. Alternatively, since `p = q`, their components must be equal, so `p.snd = q.snd`. Then applying `x` and `x_1` to both sides, we get `p.snd x x_1 = q.snd x x_1`.

